Package: gclink
Title: Gene-Cluster Discovery, Annotation and Visualization
Version: 1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Liuyang",
           family = "Li",
           email = "cyanobacteria@yeah.net",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6004-9437"))
Description:
    Performs end-to-end analysis of gene clusters—such as photosynthesis,
    carbon/nitrogen/sulfur cycling, carotenoid, antibiotic, or viral genes (capsid,
    polymerase, integrase)—from (meta)genomes or (meta)transcriptomes:
    parse Diamond/BLASTp-style results (e.g., EggNOG output is also supported),
    filter ORFs by length, detect contiguous clusters of reference genes,
    insert missing ORFs, extract genomic coordinates (optional),
    merge functional annotations, scale coordinates for plotting, and
    generate publication-ready arrow plots. Works seamlessly with or without
    CDS FASTA input and can skip plotting when functional grouping is absent.
    Citation: Li, L., Huang, D., Hu, Y., Rudling, N. M., Canniffe, D. P., Wang, F., & Wang, Y.
    "Globally distributed Myxococcota with photosynthesis gene clusters illuminate the origin
    and evolution of a potentially chimeric lifestyle." Nature Communications (2023), 14, 6450.
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-023-42193-7".
